==================================================
CHANGE — Go module restructure + docs update
Date: 2026-03-29
==================================================

==================================================
PROBLEM WITH PREVIOUS LAYOUT
==================================================

The original layout used apps/ and packages/ directories with one go.mod
per package, connected via go.work. This pattern is copied from JS/Java/Rust
monorepo conventions and is not idiomatic Go.

Problems:
  - go.work is for coordinating independently released modules, not
    co-developed intra-app packages
  - Every package needed its own go.mod, go.sum, and replace directives
  - go mod tidy had to be run per module
  - No enforced encapsulation boundary

==================================================
CHANGES MADE
==================================================

1. DIRECTORY RESTRUCTURE

  Before → After
  apps/api-server/    → cmd/api-server/
  apps/judge-worker/  → cmd/judge-worker/
  apps/local-agent/   → cmd/local-agent/
  packages/domain/    → internal/domain/
  packages/storage/   → internal/storage/
  packages/queue/     → internal/queue/
  packages/judge/     → internal/judge/
  packages/sandbox/   → internal/sandbox/
  packages/timer/     → internal/timer/
  packages/events/    → internal/events/
  packages/problemset/      → internal/problemset/
  packages/registry/        → internal/registry/
  packages/personalization/ → internal/personalization/
  packages/recommendation/  → internal/recommendation/

2. MODULE CONSOLIDATION

  Before:
    go.work                   (workspace file)
    apps/api-server/go.mod    (module: judge-loop/apps/api-server)
    apps/judge-worker/go.mod
    apps/local-agent/go.mod
    packages/domain/go.mod    (module: judge-loop/packages/domain)
    packages/storage/go.mod
    ... 14 go.mod files total

  After:
    go.mod                    (single file, module: github.com/tuannm99/judge-loop)
    go.sum                    (single file)

3. MODULE PATH

  Before: judge-loop/packages/... and judge-loop/apps/...
  After:  github.com/tuannm99/judge-loop/internal/... and .../cmd/...

  All import paths updated across all .go files via sed.

4. DOCKERFILE SIMPLIFICATION

  Before: each Dockerfile copied per-module go.mod/go.sum files separately
          and ran go work sync
  After:  each Dockerfile copies go.mod + go.sum once, then copies cmd/ and
          internal/ source, builds from ./cmd/<name>

  deploy/docker/Dockerfile.api-server     updated
  deploy/docker/Dockerfile.judge-worker   updated
  deploy/docker/Dockerfile.local-agent    updated

5. DOCKER-COMPOSE PATH FIX

  deploy/compose/docker-compose.yml:
    packages/storage/migrations → internal/storage/migrations

==================================================
WHY CMD/ AND INTERNAL/
==================================================

cmd/
  Contains only main packages (entry points). No business logic.
  Thin wiring: parse config → connect deps → start server.
  Named after the Go community convention: https://go.dev/doc/modules/layout

internal/
  All business logic lives here.
  The Go compiler enforces that no code outside this module can import
  internal/ packages. Provides encapsulation without needing separate modules.

pkg/ is NOT used — it is for code intended to be imported by external
consumers. This project has none.

